{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 02:22:49.895030", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nScope\n- Topology: 1 super-spine (AS65000), 2 spines (AS65100, AS65101), 2 leaves (AS65200, AS65201), 2 hosts (pc_0_0 on 10.0.0.0/24 and pc_0_1 on 10.0.1.0/24), EBGP everywhere, /31 interconnects at 172.16.0.0/16.\n- Focus: detect anomalies, localize faulty devices if any, and identify root cause.\n\nFindings\n\n1) End-to-end reachability (data plane)\n- Extensive cross-host pings succeed with 0% loss and low RTTs. Example:\n  - pc_0_0 → pc_0_1: 0% loss, RTT avg ~1.7–2.7 ms.\n  - Multiple other pc_0_x → pc_1_y tests also show 0% loss with RTTs ~1–5 ms.\n- No evidence of packet loss or excessive latency.\n\nAssessment: Data plane forwarding appears healthy.\n\n2) Control plane (BGP) status\n- All FRR BGP sessions are established and stable:\n  - leaf_router_0_0 (AS65200): 8 EBGP peers; PfxRcd per neighbor ≈31; Up/Down stable.\n  - leaf_router_0_1 (AS65201): 8 EBGP peers; PfxRcd per neighbor ≈31; Up/Down stable.\n  - spine_router_0_0 (AS65100): 12 EBGP peers; learns prefixes from super-spine and leaves; sessions up; no flaps seen.\n  - spine_router_0_1 (AS65101): 12 EBGP peers; sessions up; no flaps seen.\n  - super_spine_router_0 (AS65000): 32 peers; PfxRcd ≈8 per spine; all sessions established.\n- No oscillations: Up/Down timers indicate recent, steady adjacency (lab freshly started).\n- BGP path selection examples:\n  - On spine_router_0_0, 10.0.1.0/24 has multiple paths; best is directly from leaf AS65201 (shortest AS path), as expected.\n  - On spine_router_0_1, 10.0.1.0/24 learned via multiple sessions (including super-spine); best path is local leaf (AS path 65201).\n  - On leaf_router_0_0, 10.0.1.0/24 has 8 available paths; best is via neighbor 172.16.1.80 (AS path 65105 65201), selected due to “Older Path” tie-break, not ECMP.\n- Route installation is consistent with BGP:\n  - Leaves have their connected /24 and BGP-learned /24s pointing to spines.\n  - Spines have ECMP to remote pods via super-spine (e.g., multiple next-hops installed for 10.1.x/24s).\n  - Super-spine aggregates sessions and redistributes down to spines.\n\nAssessment: Control plane is converged and consistent. No stuck, idle, or flapping sessions observed.\n\n3) Routing tables (spot checks)\n- leaf_router_0_0:\n  - C>* 10.0.0.0/24 on host-facing interface.\n  - Remote 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.1.80; other remote nets via various spine neighbors.\n- leaf_router_0_1:\n  - C>* 10.0.1.0/24 on host-facing interface.\n  - Remote nets via spine neighbors (e.g., 172.16.1.2).\n- spines:\n  - Have multiple ECMP next-hops to remote pods via super-spine, and best-paths directly from local leaves where appropriate.\n\nAssessment: FIBs match BGP decisions; forwarding symmetry and reachability are intact.\n\nAbnormalities or Notable Observations\n\n- Leaf-side ECMP not used: On the leaves, for a given destination prefix, only a single best path is installed (e.g., best path chosen by “Older Path” tie-break). In a typical CLOS design, operators often enable eBGP maximum-paths to leverage ECMP at the leaf as well. Here, absence of multipath is not a functional fault but can reduce path diversity and load-sharing granularity at the leaf.\n- PfxRcd counts vary per neighbor on spines (some leaf neighbors show receiving multiple prefixes, others fewer). Given the larger lab context with many additional pods/leaves beyond the two in scope, this appears consistent with route propagation via multiple tiers and does not indicate loss of reachability.\n\nFault Localization\n- No device shows failed sessions, missing routes, or forwarding loss. All observed devices (super-spine, both spines, both leaves) are functioning within expectations.\n\nRoot Cause (for any deviations)\n- The only deviation from an idealized Clos design is lack of ECMP at the leaf. Root cause: eBGP multipath is not configured on leaves, so standard BGP best-path selection (with “Older Path” tie-break) installs a single next-hop per prefix. This is a design/optimization choice rather than a fault.\n\nOverall Health Assessment\n- Healthy. Control plane and data plane are converged and stable.\n- No functional anomalies detected that impact connectivity or performance in this scope.\n- Minor optimization note: leaf ECMP is not active, but this does not impair reachability.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 24767, "output_tokens": 5090, "total_tokens": 29857, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 0}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 3904}}}
